This paper deals with deep reinforcement learning and multi-agent environments, which are common topics in the sub-categories of artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and machine learning (cs.LG). The paper also discusses game theory and the convergence of groups of agents, which are relevant to the sub-categories of game theory (cs.GT) and multi-agent systems (cs.MA). Finally, the paper mentions reward shaping and learning from raw input pixels, which are topics in the sub-category of robotics (cs.RO).
